																		Thanks, Attribution and Other Matters
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2039383&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183047" alt="MrWrong" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2039383)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;" >MrWrong</a></span> <span class="odate time_1460252311 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">10 Apr 2016 01:38</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2488944">
									

<p>Firstly, allow me to extend thanks to those who had seen it like sirpudding, GreenWolf, minmin and TL333s. Also thanks to Athena_Grey and vezaz, who did not roll their eyes when I threw said idea onto chat.</p>
<p>This article involves the following:</p>
<ul>
<li>SCP-042 (The Formerly Winged Horse) ported over to this site by xthevilecorruptor and current version written by Skali Sharpnose</li>
<li><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/golden-horde-blues">Golden Horde Blues</a> (or at least the concept of time travelling Mongols) by vezaz</li>
<li>The Chaos Insurgency format, found <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/chaos-insurgency-hub">here</a>.</li>
</ul>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>In summary, this was written to give 042 a leash in life since it feels odd for the creature to be kept in its current state for so long.</p>
<p>Solution: Clone it.</p>
<p>To make it more interesting than having the Foundation clone it, have the CI do it. And sell them to time-travelling Mongols. 'Cos that will be really random and arbitrary, which fits in thematically with a group that wishes to promote chaos in reality (contrasting with the Foundation's &quot;order&quot;).</p>
<p>Not to mention that the CI format is really under-appreciated in general.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

