															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2039383&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183047" alt="MrWrong" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2039383)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;" >MrWrong</a></span> <span class="odate time_1460268269 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">10 Apr 2016 06:04</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2489038">
									

<p>Admittedly, I don't feel that CI's purpose in all this ought to be fully revealed. They thrive best in ambiguity, and no one (not even Delta Command) really knows what's their true endgame.</p>
<p>My personal thought would be that CI is using the time-travelling horde to break the timeline.<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-505754-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-505754-1')">1</a></sup> They could be rewriting history (be it a past event, or something in the future). Or something else.</p>
<p>Little is mentioned about the Eternal Horde here, since the CI hardly controls them. As for the CI is concerned, the Eternal Horde fits the bill for whatever ambiguous objective they have for now.</p>
<div class="footnotes-footer">
<div class="title">Footnotes</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-505754-1"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-505754-1')">1</a>. Since my headcanon is that the CI push for complete chaos instead of total order.</div>
</div>

							</div>

								
